<section class="page-panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Learning Method</p>
    <h1>Track -> Lesson -> Practice</h1>
    <p class="section-copy">LinguaJourney is designed around one simple rule: progress gets clearer when language study is planned deliberately and reviewed consistently.</p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid three-up">
    <article class="content-card">
        <h2>1. Build a track</h2>
        <p>Choose the target language, write the goal level, define the focus area, and set a milestone date with a weekly study commitment.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="content-card">
        <h2>2. Create lessons</h2>
        <p>Break the track into smaller sessions tied to vocabulary themes, skill areas, and one practical exercise you can actually complete.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="content-card">
        <h2>3. Reflect on practice</h2>
        <p>After each study session, log the new expression you learned, your confidence level, the time spent, and your next review date.</p>
    </article>
</section>
